== Hot Spring Town == Centered on the source (湯元) of the hot spring river, the town is formed by over 20 establishments including {{ill|hotels|ja|ホテル|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|ryokan|ja|旅館|12=draft|12=draft}}, souvenir shops, and restaurants. A hot spring river flows through the town, filling the area with steam and the scent of sulfur,<ref>[http://210.196.131.212/infobirds/spa/kensaku/onsenchi_detail.cfm?ID=207]{{ill|Japan Hot Spring Association|ja|日本温泉協会|12=draft|12=draft}}</ref> and there are also free foot baths as well as paid {{ill|communal baths|ja|共同浴場|1=Communal hot springs|1=Communal hot springs|1=Communal hot springs|1=Communal hot springs|1=Communal hot springs|12=draft|12=draft}}. Although the water quantity is abundant, its strongly acidic nature makes it unsuitable for recirculating equipment; therefore, all facilities use a "kakenagashi" (flow-through) system, a point some establishments proudly promote with a "Source Kakenagashi Declaration."
